  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2 (SARS-CoV-2) causes a highly contagious&#xD;
      infection with the highest viral load in the upper respiratory secretions. Despite using&#xD;
      personal protective equipment, SARS-CoV-2 contamination to the healthcare personnel is&#xD;
      possible during the airway management of infected patients. Direct laryngoscopy remains as&#xD;
      the most common method for endotracheal intubation. Our study aimed to compare the use of&#xD;
      video laryngoscopy with direct laryngoscopy for tracheal intubation in adult patients&#xD;
      receiving general anesthesia for elective surgery during the COVID-19 pandemic.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
